9:00 a.m. - Reed Arena

Master's and Doctoral Commencement and Doctoral Hooding

Saturday, May 11, 2024
  • 2:00 p.m. â Reed Arena
    • Graduate and Professional School
      • Graduates in: Architecture; Bush School of Government and Public Service; Engineering; 
        Public Health
  • 7:00 p.m. â Reed Arena
    • Graduate and Professional School
      • Graduates in: Agriculture and Life Sciences; Arts and Sciences; Mays Business School; 
        Education and Human Development; Nursing; Performance, Visualization and Fine Arts; 
        Veterinary Medicine and Biomedical Sciences

The Office of the Registrar is responsible for ensuring the number of graduates at each commencement ceremony results in ceremonies of reasonably equal duration.  Consequently, the determination of which colleges will graduate at which ceremony is announced mid-semester. Please refer to the Academic Calendar for this deadline. 

*Future events, deadlines, ceremony dates, and times are subject to change.*


Note: All students planning to participate in a commencement ceremony must do so in the ceremony designated for their college in the term in which they have an active graduation application. Graduate students can find the designated ceremony for their program on the Graduate Interdisciplinary Program page.

Spring 2024 Graduation Ceremony Information


/ Structure / News / Spring 2024 Graduation Ceremony Information
Published on 02/23/2024 03:00 PM

The end of the semester is near, and your commencement ceremony is approaching soon! The Spring 2024 commencement ceremony schedule can be found here. Guest tickets will not be required for Spring 2024 commencement.
 
A Graduation Checklist is also available online to help provide you with additional instruction and reminders.
 

Ceremony Information:

  • On the day of your ceremony, report to the north entrance of Reed Arena to check in. If you have not checked in at least 30 minutes prior to the start of your ceremony, you will be marked absent and your name will not be announced during the ceremony.
  • Disability Accommodations: Degree candidates with mobility or other disability-related needs who may require accommodations in order to participate in the ceremony should contact Laura Zeig at 979-845-1059 or graduation@tamu.edu no later than April 29, 2024.
  • As a courtesy to your fellow graduates, please be prepared to remain for the entire ceremony. The ceremony is expected to last approximately three hours.
  • Guest seating in the arena will be available on a first-come, first-served basis. Additional information regarding accessible seating and parking for guests can be found here.


Graduation Clearance and Diploma Information:

  • A final degree audit for all Spring 2024 degree candidates will be conducted on Thursday, May 9, 2024. If you clear all degree requirements at that time, your diploma will be ordered, and you can expect it to ship the week of May 27, 2024.
  • If you do not clear the initial audit, all unmet degree requirements must be resolved by 5:00 p.m. on Friday, May 31, 2024, to have your degree awarded for Spring 2024. Students who clear after the initial audit can expect their diploma to ship 2-3 weeks after their degree requirements are verified as met.
  • Diplomas will be mailed to the address included in your graduation application, upon verification of completion of all degree requirements. If you need to make any changes to the diploma mailing address on file, please email updates to degree-audit@tamu.edu as this address cannot be updated in Howdy. Please submit any changes via email no later than 5:00 p.m., Wednesday, May 8, 2024.

Answers to most questions about graduation can be found in the Graduation FAQ. Other questions regarding commencement ceremonies should be directed to the Office of the Registrar, 979-845-1059 or to graduation@tamu.edu.

Spring 2024

Click on the event title to view full event details.
NOTE: All dates and times are subject to change.

Download Calendar Options

The âDownload Semester Calendarâ function captures the current semester's Academic Calendar listings. Updates made to the Academic Calendar do not automatically synch to previously downloaded calendars. In order to capture updates, removal of a previous download will be required, followed by a re-download. 

Download Instructions - for Outlook Calendars Only
  1. Open the Outlook calendar on your device.
  2. Click the "Download Semester Calendar" button below.
  3. Double click the downloaded calendar item and look for the pop-up window in Outlook. 
  4. Select whether you would like to "Add As New" or "Import" the calendar. 
    • Select "Add As New" to add the semester calendar as a new calendar. 
      • Rename the calendar so each semester calendar has a unique name 
    • Select "Import" to add the individual semester calendar entries to your personal calendar.
Please note, Outlook displays a start/end time within the event description for calendar entries with specific deadlines.

Download Instructions - Individual Calendar Item
  1. Select the event you'd like to download.
    • You'll be directed to the events' summary details on the Texas A&M University Calendar website.
  2. Click the "Add To My Calendar" button.
  3. Select your preferred option and save item to your personal calendar.

Academic Calendar
Date Event
December 26 Tuesday. Offices reopen after semester break.
January 7 Sunday. First day of spring classes.
First day to apply for May graduation.
Undergraduate change of curriculum period begins. See Student Rule 5.1, https://student-rules.tamu.edu/rule05/.
January 11 Thursday. Last day for adding/dropping courses with no record for the spring semester, 4:30 p.m.
January 22 Monday. Official census date (12th class day).
February 1 Thursday. Undergraduate change of curriculum period ends, 4:30 p.m.
February 8 Thursday. Last day to apply for May graduation, 4:30 p.m.
February 13 Tuesday. Qatar National Sports Day (No classes; Offices closed).
February 25 - 29 Sunday - Thursday. Spring break (No classes; Offices remain open).
March 3 Sunday. Spring semester classes resume.
March 7 Thursday. Mid-semester grades due by noon, Office of Records.
March 11 Monday. Projected first day of Ramadan.*
April 7 Sunday. Last day for all students to drop courses with no academic penalty (Q-drop), 4:30 p.m.
Last day to officially withdraw from the University, 4:30 p.m.
April 11-15 Thursday-Monday. Eid Al-Fitr^* (No classes. Offices expected to be closed).
April 21 Sunday. Aggie Muster.
April 24 Wednesday. Last day of spring semester classes.
Redefined Day - Students attend their Thursday classes.
Pursuant to Student Rule 8.3 (https://student-rules.tamu.edu/rule08/), no regular course examinations (except for laboratory and one-hour courses) shall be given during the 15th week of classes.
April 25 Thursday. Reading Day (No classes: Offices remain open.)
April 28-May 1 Sunday-Wednesday. Spring semester final examinations for all students.
May 2 Thursday. Final grades due for all students by 6:00 p.m., Office of Records.
May 5 Sunday. Commencement Ceremony.
May 7 Tuesday. Qatar Foundation Convocation.*

Summer Semester 2024*

Academic Calendar
Date Event
May 19 Sunday. First day of summer classes.
First day to apply for summer graduation.
May 22 Wednesday. Official census date (4th class day).
Last day for adding/dropping courses with no record for the summer semester, 4:30 p.m.
June 6 Thursday. Last day to apply for summer graduation, 4:30 p.m.
June 18-20 Tuesday-Thursday. Eid Al-Adha^* (Offices expected to be closed).
June 16-20 Sunday-Thursday. Eid Al-Adha^* (No classes).
June 27 Thursday. Last day for all students to drop courses with no academic penalty (Q-drop), 4:30 p.m.
Last day to officially withdraw from the University, 4:30 p.m.
July 11 Thursday. Last day of summer classes.
July 14-115 Sunday-Monday. Summer term final examinations for all students.
July 17 Wednesday. Final grades due for summer term by noon, Office of Records.

*Dates are subject to change without notice.
^Dates for the Eid holidays are subject to change; however, the University will be closed for a three-day period during Eid.

title: TAMU Law Commencement
description: Spring 2024 Commencement. Date: Saturday, May 4, 2024. Time of Ceremony: 1:00 PM CST Location: Dr. Jim Vaszauskas Center for the Performing Arts,Â ...

metadata.content:
TAMU LAW COMMENCEMENT

 

There are three commencement ceremonies throughout the year for Texas A&M University School of Law graduates. Below are three tabs with additional information about each ceremony.

 

Spring 2024 Commencement

Date: Saturday, May 4, 2024
Time of Ceremony: 1:00 PM CST
Location: Dr. Jim Vaszauskas Center for the Performing Arts, 1110 W. Debbie Lane, Mansfield, TX 76063 

 

Regalia information can be found on the Student Graduation Checklist.

 

A live stream of the commencement will be shown on this webpage once doors open for the event.

 

Additional Information

  • Student Graduation Checklist 
  • Frequently Asked Questions 
  • Disability Accommodations 
  • Photo Gallery of Dr. Jim Vaszauskas Center for the Performing Arts 

Important Deadlines

  • June 1, 2023: File degree plan for LLM and MLS programs for December 2023 degree
  • November 1, 2023: File degree plan for LLM and MLS programs for May 2024 degree
  • February 16, 2024: Last day to apply for May graduation without a late fee for JD, LLM, and MLS programs
  • March 18, 2024: Pro bono deadline for May 2024 JD graduates
  • March 25, 2024: Deadline to:
    • Complete the commencement attendance survey
    • Confirm or change name and address on Howdy
    • Remove directory holds to have name printed in commencement program
    • Request ADA accommodations for graduates and guests for the commencement ceremony
    • JD - apply for concentrations to be recognized at commencement
    • LLM and MLS - Ensure certificates are included in your curriculum information in Howdy to be recognized at commencement
  • April 1, 2024: Deadline to:
    • File degree plan for LLM and MLS programs for August 2024 degree
  • April 7, 2024: Deadline to order regalia
  • April 30, 2024: Deadline to:
    • Apply for May degree for JD, LLM, and MLS
    • LLM and MLS - Apply for certificates
  • May 4, 2024: Commencement ceremony for JD, LLM, and MLS degrees

Summer commencement for August graduates is held by Texas A&M University located in College Station, Texas. The School of Law does not oversee any part of the summer commencement.

For information about summer commencement ceremonies in College Station, including dates, deadlines, checklist, accommodations, regalia, etc., please see https://graduation.tamu.edu/.

All questions about the summer commencement ceremony should be emailed to graduation@tamu.edu. 

Fall commencement for December graduates is held by Texas A&M University located in College Station, Texas. The School of Law does not oversee any part of the fall commencement.

For information about fall commencement ceremonies in College Station, including dates, deadlines, checklist, accommodations, regalia, etc., please see https://graduation.tamu.edu/.

All questions about the fall commencement ceremony should be emailed to graduation@tamu.edu.

Fort Worth, Texas 76102-6509

Toll Free: 800.733.9529

Spring  2024 Commencement

See important upcoming dates for graduates.

Ready for graduation? Take a minute to prepare!

Congratulations on approaching the finish line of your university career! Whatever path the next phase of  your life takes you, you're completing an important milestone with the completion of your degree... but there's one important checkpoint before you go:

Complete your application to graduate now!

Step-by-step: Complete your
graduation application!

You've probably already completed a graduation checklist with your academic advisor. But the graduation checklist is not the same as applying for graduation.

To graduate, you must complete an application to graduate. There's an application fee involved, a deadline, and the possibility for late fees if you are not complete in time.

The non-refundable Graduation Application Fee is $50 for all applicants who apply before the application deadline. Fees are to be paid at the Business Office (FH 108C.) Students who do not apply by the Application Deadline will be assessed an additional $20 late fee and will be eligible for conferral only.

Graduation: Spring 2024

  • Ceremony Date: 3 pm, May 11, 2024
  • Location: Cadence Bank Center, 301 W Loop 121, Belton, TX 76513
  • Application Deadline: March 29, 2024
  • Graduation Orientation: 10 am and 5:30 pm May 8; Bernie Beck Lecture Hall in Founders Hall.
  • Graduation Fair: Noon to 5:30 pm March 6; Bill Yowell Conference Center in Warrior Hall.

Graduation: Summer 2024

  • Ceremony Date: August 9, 2024
  • Location: Bill Yowell Conference Center in Warrior Hall, 10 am
  • Application Deadline: July 5, 2024
  • Graduation Orientation: 10 am and 5:30 pm August 7; Bernie Beck Lecture Hall in Founders Hall.
  • Graduation Fair: Noon to 5:30 pm March 6; Bill Yowell Conference Center in Warrior Hall.

Links for Graduates!

  • Talk to your academic advisor
  • Order your cap and gown
  • Find graduation gifts at the bookstore
  • Buy your class ring!
  • Continue your journey as an A&M-Central Texas Alumnus. Join the Alumni Association.
  • Planning for Spring 2024 Graduation

Video for Commencement ceremonies are typically posted to our YouTube channel a few days after commencement:  Subscribe, enjoy and stay in touch!

Graduation

  1. Home
  2. Students
  3. Graduation

On behalf of the school, congratulations on entering the final semester of your curriculum at SPH! To help you prepare for graduation, please review the information below for the required forms and deadlines. 

Applying for Your Diploma

You must file an application for degree before you can graduate. Students planning to graduate must submit the graduation application online in the Howdy portal. The application for spring 2024 graduation opens December 18 and the last day to apply online to avoid a late fee is February 16. The last day to submit an application online for graduation is March 27, and in person via a paper application, April 30. In addition, Texas A&M provides a Graduation Checklist, which upcoming graduates are strongly recommended to review and complete the necessary steps.

Commencement Ceremony

Commencement

Undergraduate Students in the School of Public Health

Commencement for all undergraduate students in the School of Public Health will be Saturday, May 11 at 9:00 AM in Reed Arena.

Master's and Doctoral Degree Commencement and Hooding

Commencement and hooding ceremony for all graduate students (master's and doctoral) in the School of Public Health will be Saturday, May 11at 2:00 PM in Reed Arena.

Additional information for each ceremony can be found here.

Please note that all ceremony dates are subject to change.

Parking information is available on the Transportation Services website. For accommodations, visit the Texas A&M Graduation website.

Ordering Regalia

Students who need to order regalia should consult the Regalia: Cap & Gown website for more information: The color of the hood for graduate-level degrees is based on your degree.

SPH Graduation Celebration

In recognition of your graduation we invite you to attend the SPH Graduation Celebration. The celebration will be held at the School of Public Health, at 212 Adriance Lab Road, from 11:00 AM to 1:00 PM.  Please bring your friends and family to meet faculty, staff and administration. You will also be able to collect your graduation gift from the School as well as have photo taken.  An official invitation will be sent via email at a later date.

Graduation Survey

The school compiles data on employment plans of our graduates for CEPH accreditation requirements. Personal information will be kept confidential and is only used for statistical purposes. Individual student data will not be published or shared. The survey will be sent to students' TAMU and exchange email accounts directly.

Additional Resources

  • Financial Aid: consider meeting with a Financial Aid or Money Wise advisor to plan for loan repayment and deferment options (if applicable).
  • Association of Former Students, Aggie Ring: connect with Aggies around the world by purchasing a class ring. Review the website for eligibility requirements. Also update your information in the Aggie Network portal to receive important information from the Association and your class agents.
  • SPH Alumni Association: join this network to receive information from SPH after you graduate.
  • LinkedIn: become a member of our private LinkedIn group where we share additional resources, job postings and messages from SPH.
